                                     {
                                         "text":  "<p><h3>Human Migration</h3>Our species emerged somewhere in Africa between 350,000 and 200,000 years ago, according to fossil evidence. However, the migration out of Africa did not happen immediately. Around 70,000 to 50,000 years ago, Homo sapiens began migrating to different regions of Asia. Fossils also indicate another major migration between 45,000 and 35,000 years ago, moving towards the European continent and northeastern Asia",
                                         "source":  [
                                                        {
                                                            "type":  1,
                                                            "uuid":  "2be849f1-551b-44eb-8fc6-87027dbf8a68",
                                                            "text":  "Mounier, A., & Mirazón Lahr, M.",
                                                            "page":  "",
