                                         "PostMention":  "."
                                     },
                                     {
                                         "text":  "Regarding the arrival to the Americas (<i>Abya Yala</i>), current evidence suggests that the first humans arrived sometime between 30,000 and 22,000 years ago, likely through multiple migratory waves. Recent studies on the Mapuche people, for example, indicate at least two major migrations toward the southern regions of the continent",
                                         "source":  [
                                                        {
                                                            "type":  1,
                                                            "uuid":  "ed998d95-1afb-4021-9181-2c81d1d9ecd5",
                                                            "text":  "Arango-Isaza, E., et al.",
                                                            "page":  "",
                                                            "date_time":  {
                                                                              "type":  "gregory",
                                                                              "year":  "2023",
                                                                              "month":  "",
                                                                              "day":  ""
                                                                          }
                                                        },
                                                        {
                                                            "type":  1,
                                                            "uuid":  "064c3691-1f4c-491b-b643-150c011b4525",
                                                            "text":  "Goebel, Ted, et al.",
                                                            "page":  "",
                                                            "date_time":  {
                                                                              "type":  "gregory",
                                                                              "year":  "2008",
                                                                              "month":  "",
                                                                              "day":  ""
                                                                          }
                                                        },
                                                        {
                                                            "type":  1,
                                                            "uuid":  "cff99ec5-cb25-40ef-b2ee-410a75e73a6e",
                                                            "text":  "National Geographic Education",
                                                            "page":  "",
                                                            "date_time":  {
                                                                              "type":  "gregory",
                                                                              "year":  "",
                                                                              "month":  "",
                                                                              "day":  ""
                                                                          }
                                                        }
                                                    ],
                                         "date_time":  null,
                                         "isTable":  false,
                                         "imgdesc":  "",
                                         "format":  "html",
                                         "PostMention":  "."
                                     },
                                     {
                                         "text":  "The description of human origins and their dispersion over millennia was traditionally based on written narratives, which, in the most optimistic estimates, projected only 177 generations since the ‘origin’ of our species. With advances in knowledge and DNA analysis techniques, we have gained a clearer understanding of our migrations, and today we can more accurately estimate that the number of human generations is around 8,000",
                                         "source":  [
                                                        {
                                                            "type":  1,
                                                            "uuid":  "eda6e242-751a-46b3-b5f7-0c4489d9b374",
                                                            "text":  "History Tracers Team",
